######################################
#  Adventuron                        #
######################################

######################################
#  Game Information                  #
######################################

game_information {

   game_name        = The Silver Key
   game_shortname   = Silver Key
   written_by       = David Culp
   year_of_original = 2024
   year_of_release  = 2024
   uuid             = 
   short_synopsis   = Solve the adventure
   game_version     = 0.1.0
   
}

start_at = forest_clearing

######################################
#  Locations                         #
######################################

locations 
{

   forest_clearing : location "You stand in a tranquil forest clearing, surrounded by towering trees whose branches weave a canopy above. In the center of the clearing stands a massive, ancient oak tree, its gnarled roots twisting and sprawling across the ground like the fingers of some long-forgotten giant. " ;
   
   dungeon_entrance : location "You stand at the entrance to a dark and forbidding dungeon. The massive stone entrance looms before you, its surface etched with strange, weathered runes that seem to shift in the dim light. Vines and moss cling to the cracks in the stone, as if nature itself is trying to seal the horrors within. A faint, cold draft seeps from the edges of the door, carrying with it the unmistakable scent of damp earth,decay, and death." ;
    
   treasure_room : location "You step into the treasure room, and a soft golden light fills the chamber, illuminating piles of glittering coins, ornate jewelry, and ancient artifacts scattered across the stone floor. The air is thick with the scent of old parchment and polished metal, and the faint hum of magic seems to resonate in the walls. In the center of the room sits a grand chest, its lid slightly ajar, revealing a tantalizing glimpse of untold riches within." ;
    
   tool_shed : location "You find yourself in a shadowy corner of the forest where the trees seem to lean unnaturally close, their twisted branches forming an almost sentient archway. To the north stands a strange structure that wasn’t here before—a small, alien-looking shed. Its walls, though resembling weathered wood, shimmer faintly with a texture that shifts under your gaze, as if it doesn’t quite belong to this world. The door is tightly shut, sealed with a rusted lock that pulses faintly with an eerie light. The ground around the shed is untouched, as though it has simply appeared, defying the passage of time and nature itself." ;
   
   inside_tool_shed : location "The rundown tool shed is dimly lit, with shafts of light streaming through the gaps in the rotting wooden walls. Rusted tools hang haphazardly on the walls, and the air smells faintly of mildew and damp earth." ;
} // end locations


######################################
#  Booleans                          #
######################################

booleans 
{
   has_silver_key_been_found : boolean "false"; // False is the default
}

######################################
#  Connections                       #
######################################

connections 
{

   from, direction, to = [
      forest_clearing, east, dungeon_entrance,
      dungeon_entrance, east, treasure_room,
      forest_clearing, north, tool_shed
      tool_shed, north, inside_tool_shed,
   ]
   
}// end connections

######################################
#  Objects                           #
######################################

objects 
{

   shovel : object "a shovel" at = "inside_tool_shed"
      msg = "A sturdy shovel lies here, perfect for digging." ;

   silver_key : object "a silver key" 
      msg = "A beautifully engraved silver key, unearthed from beneath the oak tree." ;

   torch : object "a torch" at = "dungeon_entrance"
      msg = "A simple torch. It looks like it could be useful in dark places." ;

   lit_torch : object "a torch" 
      msg = "A blazing torch to light your way through the darkness." ;
      
   treasure : scenery "treasure" at = "treasure_room"
      msg = "Piles of gold coins and glittering gems. This is the treasure you’ve been seeking!" ;
      
   iron_gate : scenery "an iron gate" at = "dungeon_entrance" 
      msg ="A large iron gate blocks the entrance to the dungeon.  The gate appears to be locked.";
      
   genie_lamp : object "a golden genie lamp" at="dungeon_entrance" msg = "The golden genie lamp gleams with an otherworldly glow, its surface smooth and inviting as if waiting to be touched.";
   
   shed_key : object "a brass key" msg = "A plain brass key, unremarkable in every way." ;
      
   
}//end objects

######################################
#  barriers                          #
######################################

barriers 
{

   dungeon_entrance : block_path 
   {
      from                 = dungeon_entrance
      to                   = treasure_room
      block_when_exists    = iron_gate
      message              = "The iron gate is locked and you cannot enter the dungeon."
    }// end dungeon_entrance
    
   treasure_room : block_path 
   {
      from                    = dungeon_entrance
      to                      = treasure_room
      block_when_not_carried  = lit_torch
      message                 = "It seems to dark to enter the dungeon."
    }//end treasure room
    
   shed_room : door 
   {
      from                    = tool_shed
      to                      = inside_tool_shed
      key                     = shed_key
    }//end shed room
}// end barriers

######################################
#  Commands                          #
######################################

on_command 
{
   : match "use shovel ; dig hole; dig shovel"  
   {
      : if (is_at "forest_clearing" && is_carried "shovel") 
      {
         : print   "You dig at the base of the tree and uncover a silver key." ;
         : create "silver_key" ;
         : set_true "has_silver_key_been_found"; 
      } // END IF
      : else_if (is_carried "shovel") 
      {
         : print "You dig but find nothing.";
      }// end else if
   }// end match

   : match "use key; unlock gate; open gate"  
   {
      : if (is_at "dungeon_entrance" && is_carried "silver_key") 
      {
         : print   "You open the iron gate and the dark dungeon lies before you." ;
         : destroy "silver_key" ;
         : destroy "iron_gate" ;
      }// end if
   }// end match
   
   : match "light torch"  
   {
      : if (is_at "dungeon_entrance" && is_carried "torch") 
      {
         : print   "You light the torch illuminating the way before you." ;
         : destroy "torch" ;
         : create "lit_torch" target = "inventory" ;
      }// end if
   }//end match
   
   : match "rub lamp"  
   {
      : if (is_carried "genie_lamp") 
      {
         : print   "As you rub the golden lamp, a faint warmth spreads through your hand, and a soft, swirling mist escapes from its spout. Suddenly, with a small clink, a nondescript brass key falls to the ground at your feet.  The lamp disappears in apuuf of golden flame and smoke" ;
         : destroy "genie_lamp" ;
         : create "shed_key" ;
      }// end if
   }//end match
  
}// end on_command

######################################
#  On describe                     #
######################################
on_describe 
{

   : if (is_at "treasure_room" ) 
   {
      : print "CONGRATULATIONS YOU FOUND THE TREASURE. YOU WIN!" ;
      : win_game ;
   }// end if treasure_room
   
   : if (is_at "inside_tool_shed" && is_carried "shovel" == false ) 
   {
      : print "A sturdy looking shovel leans against the wall of the shed.";
   }// end if toolshed
   
   : if (is_at "dungeon_entrance" && is_present "iron_gate") 
   {
      : print "A massive iron gate with a large lock blocks your way." ;
      
   }// end if dungeon entracne
   
   : if (is_at "forest_clearing" && has_silver_key_been_found == false) 
   {
      : print "The earth beneath the oak looks oddly disturbed, as though something has been buried there long ago. A faint glint of sunlight catches on something near the base of the tree." ;
   }
   : else_if (is_at "forest_clearing" && has_silver_key_been_found == true)
   {
      :print "You see a freshly dug hole at the base of the ancient oak tree.";
   }//end if

}// end on describe
   



assets {
   graphics {
      forest_clearing : base64_png "";
      dungeon_entrance : base64_png "";
      treasure_room : base64_png "";
      tool_shed : base64_png "";
      inside_tool_shed : base64_png "";
   }
}
